{
  "texts": [
    "Energy obeys all laws of thermodynamics, while information may not.",
    "When energy and information of systems interact, novel properties or levels of energy and information may emerge.",
    "Information can reveal itself in different forms (as entropy, order, complexity, physically encoded, mechanical, biological, structural, in neural or social networks, etc.).",
    "Information may increase free energy by reducing entropy in an open system, or by capturing free energy from the surroundings.",
    "The dynamics of information and energy has been studied mostly in physical chemistry and engineering."
  ]
}